  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PR Strategist",
  "description": "<p>The Marketing and Public Relations Executive will be in charge of developing and executing international branding campaigns from scratch for our umbrella of e-commerce brands.<br /></p><p>The goal will be to secure high-value partnerships that will help boost our brand reputation & ultimately help us increase sales internationally. We are looking to build great partnerships with both businesses & individuals to help build our competitive advantage, and need your help to do so.<br /></p><p>The role is fast-paced, and hands-on and will require a high degree of adaptability, responsibility and project management.<br /></p><p>You will be given a lot more autonomy and decision-making power compared to similar roles in MNCs, and you will directly see the fruit of your labour, being the spearhead of all Public Relations efforts.</p><p>Your role will be to develop & execute these high-value collaborations/partnerships/branding campaign end-to-end.<br /></p><p>You will come up with list of potential partnerships, narrow down which brands we want to collaborate with, come up with a strategy to secure this collaborations & execute your plan.<br /></p><p>You will be working with large media companies from across the globe, influencers, working professionals (e.g. professional athletes) and other brands.<br /></p><p>On top of securing high-value partnerships, you will spearhead content creation for our brands (i.e. blog articles/content)<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Generating, researching, and pitching ideas for written contents</li><li>Writing, editing, publishing, and promoting content. (English and other languages)</li><li>Promoting new posts using advertisements, emails, social media, and other methods to alert and attract new readers.</li><li>Advocating and educating others about interests, products, or services.</li><li>Inviting other bloggers, experts, or other notable guests to contribute content to the webpage.</li><li>Will also be looking to secure high-value partnerships/collaborations internationally, beginning with Australia's market.</li><li>Monitoring responses to posts via the website, social media, or other platforms to better understand the audience.</li><li>Staying current on industry trends for possible opportunities to attract new readers or create stronger, more engaging content.</li></ul>",
